ffect in accordance with reg. 1(2) of the amending S.I.) by <ref eId="rnbeycg5-d3e29915a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2016/909">The Benefit Cap (Housing Benefit and Universal Credit) (Amendment) Regulations 2016 (S.I. 2016/909)</ref>, <ref eId="rnbeycg5-d3e29918a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2016/909/regulation/1/1">regs. 1(1)</ref>, <ref eId="rnbeycg5-d3e29921a1310" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2016/909/regulation/3/4">3(4)</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-781ff9d386de00ad3cc27d1b1c688c0c" marker="F2"><p>Sum in <ref eId="rnbeycg5-d3e27040a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/regulation/80A/2/a">Reg. 80A(2)(a)</ref>  substituted (1.4.2023) by <ref eId="rnbeycg5-d3e27043a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2023/335">The Benefit Cap (Annual Limit) (Amendment) Regulations 2023 (S.I. 2023/335)</ref>, <ref eId="rnbeycg5-d3e27046a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2023/335/regulation/1/2">regs. 1(2)</ref>, <ref eId="rnbeycg5-d3e27049a1310" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2023/335/regulation/3/a">3(a)</ref> (with <ref eId="rnbeycg5-d3e27052a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2023/335/regulation/1/3">reg. 1(3)</ref>)</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-a057916d811d63c795926fddc2cc28ec" marker="F3"><p>Sum in <ref eId="rnbeycg5-d3e28213a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/regulation/80A/2/b">Reg. 80A(2)(b)</ref>  substituted (1.4.2023) by <ref eId="rnbeycg5-d3e28216a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2023/335">The Benefit Cap (Annual Limit) (Amendment) Regulations 2023 (S.I. 2023/335)</ref>, <ref eId="rnbeycg5-d3e28219a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2023/335/regulation/1/2">regs. 1(2)</ref>, <ref eId="rnbeycg5-d3e28222a1310" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2023/335/regulation/3/b">3(b)</ref> (with <ref eId="rnbeycg5-d3e28225a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2023/335/regulation/1/3">reg. 1(3)</ref>)</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-0441afc9f3871a1ff524998092c64fe0" marker="F4"><p>Sum in <ref eId="rnbeycg5-d3e23192a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/regulation/80A/2/c">Reg. 80A(2)(c)</ref>  substituted (1.4.2023) by <ref eId="rnbeycg5-d3e23195a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2023/335">The Benefit Cap (Annual Limit) (Amendment) Regulations 2023 (S.I. 2023/335)</ref>, <ref eId="rnbeycg5-d3e23198a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2023/335/regulation/1/2">regs. 1(2)</ref>, <ref eId="rnbeycg5-d3e23201a1310" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2023/335/regulation/3/c">3(c)</ref> (with <ref eId="rnbeycg5-d3e23204a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2023/335/regulation/1/3">reg. 1(3)</ref>)</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-6053ce4c0f5188e04c415703bdb861e3" marker="F5"><p>Sum in <ref eId="rnbeycg5-d3e26139a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/regulation/80A/2/d">Reg. 80A(2)(d)</ref>  substituted (1.4.2023) by <ref eId="rnbeycg5-d3e26142a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2023/335">The Benefit Cap (Annual Limit) (Amendment) Regulations 2023 (S.I. 2023/335)</ref>, <ref eId="rnbeycg5-d3e26145a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2023/335/regulation/1/2">regs. 1(2)</ref>, <ref eId="rnbeycg5-d3e26148a1310" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2023/335/regulation/3/d">3(d)</ref> (with <ref eId="rnbeycg5-d3e26151a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2023/335/regulation/1/3">reg. 1(3)</ref>)</p></note></notes><proprietary xmlns:ukm="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/namespaces/metadata" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:dct="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" source="#"><dc:identifier>http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2013/376/regulation/80A/2025-04-01</dc:identifier><dc:title>The Universal Credit Regulations 2013</dc:title><dc:type>text</dc:type><dc:format>text/xml</dc:format><dc:language>en</dc:language><dc:publisher>Statute Law Database</dc:publisher><dc:subject>SOCIAL SECURITY</dc:subject><dc:modified>2026-03-19</dc:modified><dc:contributor>Expert Participation</dc:contributor><dct:valid>2025-03-21</dct:valid><dc:description>These Regulations contain provisions in relation to universal credit under Part 1 of the Welfare Reform Act 2012 (c.5) (“the Act”). They also include provision for a benefit cap under section 96 of the Act.</dc:description><ukm:SecondaryMetadata><ukm:DocumentClassification><ukm:DocumentCategory Value="secondary"/><ukm:DocumentMainType Value="UnitedKingdomStatutoryInstrument"/><ukm:DocumentStatus Value="revised"/><ukm:DocumentMinorType Value="regulation"/></ukm:DocumentClassification><ukm:Year Value="2013"/><ukm:Number Value="376"/><ukm:Made Date="2013-02-25"/><ukm:ComingIntoForce><ukm:DateTime Date="2013-04-29"/></ukm:ComingIntoForce><ukm:ISBN Value="9780111535271"/><ukm:UnappliedEffects><ukm:UnappliedEffect AffectingURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2018/65" AffectedYear="2013" Type="words omitted" AffectingYear="2018" EffectId="key-d8f79d3b9d8eda2a95d629146c960ea2" AffectingNumber="65" AffectedProvisions="Table of Contents" Row="5" AffectingEffectsExtent="E+W+S" Modified="2021-07-06T15:44:13Z" AffectedURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376" AffectingClass="UnitedKingdomStatutoryInstrument" Notes="This amendment not applied to legislation.gov.uk. The table of contents for this legislation will be 